Nicholas Pembyrton or Pemerton was buried in the seventh

bay of the Choir in S. Mary Chapel. The organ was presumably at the extreme west end of the Chapel. Grey Friars, p. 87.

1520. MARGARET ASSHELEY. To be buried “in the same place wher the body of my housbande Edwarde Asshelay now restith.'' Bequeathed to each Order of Friars at her burial, 6s. ssd.

Will dated 25 May, 1520. Proved 26 June, 1520. 31 Ayloffe.

She was buried by her husband, who died in 1518 (see p. 129 above), before the Common Altar. Grey Friars, p. 1 1 0.
